<br />
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This deck contains only cards found in the 2 starters and is thus very easy for a beginner to construct.  <br />
<br />
Start with Faramir, Merry, and Pippin.  Discard Merry and Pippin as necessary and draw additional copies to play later.  After Aragorn, Wingfoot comes out, try to keep Merry and Pippin around with stealth cards so you can wound minions when you move.<br />
<br />
Ancient Roads and Anborn will make the minions roaming so that the Rangers of Ithilien get their strength boost and the Ranger&#39;s Bow will can deliver its wounds.<br />
<br />
On the shadow side, Dark Fury will pump up the Dundand minions while Gnawing, Biting, Hacking, Burning will help you build a small swarm of Isengard Orcs for play at later sites.<br />
<br />
It&#39;s easy to build and easy to play.  Faramir and Aragorn Combined is a great beginner deck!<br />
 </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
